<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-02T11:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-02T11:40:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/958: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-02T12:00:00-04:40">February 2,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2. Department’s circular telegram February 1, 7 p.m. Minister of Foreign
                            Affairs informs me that at the instance of the Brazilian Government the
                            Dominican Government on January 30 telegraphed the Peruvian Government
                            supporting Brazilian proposal for the settlement of Leticia controversy
                            as fair and reasonable and urging its acceptance by Peru.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>